==English==

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ʌdʒ|-ʌdʒ]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

#{{countable}} Deep-seated anger towards someone or about something.

====Usage note====
You would usually either [[hold a grudge]], [[have a grudge]], or [[bear a grudge]] against someone.

====Translations====
{{top}}
*Danish: [[nag]], [[uvilje]]
*Finnish: [[kauna]]
{{mid}}
*German: [[Groll]] {{m}}, [[Neid]] {{m}}
{{bottom}}

====Related terms====
*[[grudge match]]

===Verb===
{{en-verb|grudg|ing}}

#To be [[unwilling]] to [[give]] or [[allow]].
:''I do not grudge him his success.''
:''His cruel master grudged him even the food he ate.''
:''I grudge paying ten pounds for a bottle of wine which isn't worth five pounds.

